Structs/ModelPerformance.html.name: ModelPerformance
Structs/ModelPerformance.html.abstract: Structure representing performance setting for tasks related to specific ML model. It’s defined as a combination of mode and rate.

Protocols/VisionManagerDelegate.html#/s:.abstract: Tells the delegate that new detections are available.

Protocols/ARDataProvider.html.name: ARDataProvider
Protocols/ARDataProvider.html.abstract: Interface for AR relative data provider. It used for commutication between VisionSDK and VisionAR frameworks.

Protocols/VisionManagerDelegate.html.name: VisionManagerDelegate
Protocols/VisionManagerDelegate.html.abstract: The interface that user’s custom object should conform to in order to receive events from SDK.

Protocols/VisionManagerARDelegate.html.name: VisionManagerARDelegate
Protocols/VisionManagerARDelegate.html.abstract: The interface that allows to receive instructions on how to render navigation route. Object that implements this interface is supposed to display navigation route based on provided instructions.

Protocols/VisionPresentationControllable.name: VisionPresentationControllable
Protocols/VisionPresentationControllable.abstract: The interface that allows managing the presentation state of provided visual components.

Enums/ModelPerformanceMode.html#/s:9Visi.name: dynamic
Enums/ModelPerformanceMode.html#/s:9Visi.abstract: Dynamic. It depends on speed. Variable from ModelPerformanceRate.low (0 km/h) to VisionManager’s performance property (90 km/h).

Enums/ModelPerformanceMode.html.name: ModelPerformanceMode
Enums/ModelPerformanceMode.html.abstract: Enumeration which determines whether SDK should adapt its performance to environmental changes (acceleration/deceleration, standing time) or stay fixed.

Enums/ModelPerformanceRate.html.name: ModelPerformanceRate
Enums/ModelPerformanceRate.html.abstract: Enumeration which determines performance rate of the specific model. These are high-level settings that translates into adjustment of FPS for ML model inference.

Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.name: delegate
Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.abstract: The delegate receiving events from SDK. This is a custom object that user of the SDK provides.

Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.name: arDelegate
Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.abstract: Set delegate which will receive and handle instructions on rendering AR navigation.

Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.name: detectionPerformance
Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.abstract: Used for configuration of detection-related tasks performance.

Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.name: estimatedPosition
Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.abstract: Current position estimated by SDK defined as a set of location-related parameters.

Classes/VisionManager.html#/s:9VisionSDK.abstract: Create and setup presentation objects. Caller may configure presentation with presenter and display platform-specific view component.

Classes/VisionManager.html.abstract: The main object for registering for events from the library, starting and stopping their delivery. It also provides some useful function for performance configuration and data conversion.
